correctness.rationale: Several major issues and schema violations. Key errors: (1) Film thickness is incorrect and unit-mismatched: 600 cycles × 1.66 Å ≈ 996 Å (~100 nm) per article; extraction reports 980 nm (10× too large). (2) Substrate mismatch: 600-cycle patterned-film result (980 Å) was on silicon with native oxide, but extraction lists borosilicate glass slides. (3) Flow rates are wrong: values 100 and 35 were partial pressures (mTorr) from IV-B, not sccm; mapping them to SCM-PER-MIN violates factual alignment. (4) Multiple nulls where schema expects objects (plasmaPower, supercycleDesign, absorptionCoefficient, bandGap, resistivity, carrierDensity, subthresholdSwing, onOffRatio), which violates the schema; optional fields should be omitted if unknown. (5) Roughness likely unit error: article’s 17.3 RMS corresponds to ~17.3 Å (≈1.73 nm) for a 200 Å film; extraction uses 17.3 nm. (6) Uniformity set to 50% appears to misread 50 mV threshold variation; no thickness-uniformity percent is provided. (7) Conformality aspect ratio set to 0.0 and filmDensity set to 0.0 are unsupported. (8) Film composition fields include 0% and a generic 1:1 ratio without evidence; should be omitted or populated with actual characterization. (9) Pressure set to 760 mmHg is inferred (open-air operation) but not explicitly reported; mark as such or omit. (10) Saturation=True and nucleationPeriod=0 are not supported for ZnO under the stated conditions. Correct or remove these fields; align filmThickness, substrate, flowRates/units, roughness units, and avoid nulls/placeholder values to meet schema and article traceability.

completeness.rationale: Several key issues reduce completeness and schema compliance. (1) Missing processes: The article reports at least two distinct ZnO SALD conditions that should be separate processes: (a) TFT semiconductor deposition (DEZ ~310 mTorr; water with ~6 Torr NH3 in oxidant; 63 ms residence; GPC ~1.7 Å; 176 cycles; ~300 Å thickness) and (b) the selective-deposition/discrimination/patterning runs (DEZ 100 mTorr; H2O 35 mTorr; 63 ms; GPC 1.66 Å; 600 cycles gives ~980 Å). Only one process is extracted and it mixes/omits important details. (2) Incorrect/unsupported values: filmThickness is given as 980 nm but the article reports ~980 Å (~98 nm) for 600 cycles; flowRates are populated with values that are actually partial pressures (100 and 35 mTorr) and use sccm units—this is unit/semantic misuse; uniformity.variation set to 50% is not reported (article mentions threshold-voltage uniformity, not thickness uniformity); conformality.aspectRatio set to 0 is unsupported; saturation=True for ZnO is not explicitly stated. (3) Missing reactants: NH3 dopant in the oxidant stream during TFT ZnO growth is not captured (co-reactant lists only water). (4) Schema violations/traceability: Many fields are null or placeholders (“Not Found”), e.g., plasmaPower, absorptionCoefficient, bandGap, resistivity, carrierDensity, subthresholdSwing, onOffRatio, safety; schema expects objects or omission, not nulls/placeholder strings. filmComposition is populated with 0% and an assumed 1:1 atomic ratio without characterization—these are not traceable to the article. supercycleDesign and plasmaPower are present as nulls, which violates the object types. (5) Reactor manufacturer and carrier/purging gas types are not provided in the article but are required by the schema fields; using “Not Found” does not satisfy traceability. To improve completeness, add a second process for the TFT ZnO deposition, correct film thickness units, remove nulls and unsupported placeholders, represent NH3 as a co-reactant, fix flow/pressure fields (or omit flow rates if not reported), and only include characterization-derived composition/uniformity if supported by the text.
